The paper deals with the computational complexity of planar valued constraint satisfaction problems (VCSPs), which involve graphs and constraints. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with algorithms, data structures, artificial intelligence, computational geometry, and machine learning. Specifically, cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CC (computational complexity), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.CG (computational geometry), and cs.LG (machine learning) are all relevant sub-categories for this paper.
